1
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:16,683
Setback

2
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:49,090
Religious freedom now!

3
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,884
"Stop religious persecution"
"Trigger is fake news"

4
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:53,511
Cutting in… one, two, three.

5
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:55,388
BUILDING COMPLETION CEREMONY

6
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,064
On this day, I, Koo Hyeongtae,

7
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:06,357
am declaring an all-out war
on misinformation.

8
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:08,735
We'll be working with law enforcement

9
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:11,446
to get to the bottom
of this vile act of cyberterrorism.

10
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:14,199
No. Please don't jump to
any conclusions

11
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:15,909
before you've heard
both sides of the story.

12
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:17,077
No, we're not responsible

13
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,203
-for what happened with the Haven--
-Hang up.

14
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:19,996
Didn't I tell you
not to take these prank calls?

15
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,248
- Ms. Hong.
- What are you doing, Ms. Hong?

16
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,000
-You wanted to take those?
-No!

17
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:25,460
What is this, North Korea?

18
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:26,920
Who's even watching this anyway?

19
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:29,339
And to our employees,
your full cooperation is much appreciated.

20
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,801
Songi said it's the anniversary
of her mom's death.

21
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:34,177
Has anyone seen her yet?

22
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:36,137
Her mom is dead? When'd that happen?

23
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:37,347
Songi's only in her early twenties.

24
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:40,183
Sweetie, you type fast,
and you're great at what you do,

25
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:42,644
but your cheekbones do stick out a bit.

26
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:44,395
Physiognomy tells me you like to pry.

27
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,772
Maybe facial contouring would help?

28
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:47,565
Nope, but chopping off your tongue would.

29
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,067
Oh, and about the raunchy video
from yesterday.

30
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,193
I don't think that was a deepfake.

31
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:51,402
Ms. Hong, do you think--

32
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:59,661
Whoa, is it "bring your dog to work" day?

33
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:02,413
Oh, you're the new guy, right?

34
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:04,499
I'm Seo Jeongseok. Nice to meet you.

35
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:06,084
Sorry, my hands are sweaty.

36
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,044
My name is Han Do.

37
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:12,173
My name's Yoon Byeonggeun. I'm a producer.

38
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:14,676
I'm your senior,
so I'd recommend shaking my hand.

39
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,356
Oh hey, what's with the funeral getup?

40
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,482
You really don't know?

41
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:32,110
They're rounding everyone up
because of yesterday's incident.

42
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:33,194
President Koo's a natural

43
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,863
when it comes to
putting out fires like this.

44
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:37,490
If someone told me
he majored in media firefighting,

45
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:38,867
-I'd believe it.
-Media firefighting, yeah.

46
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,368
He was so quick to respond,
it's almost as if

47
00:02:40,451 --> 00:02:43,288
he knew this would happen.
It's a little suspicious.

48
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:44,831
You think President Koo is Dr. Trigger?

49
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:45,915
No way, man.

50
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,710
He might hold a deep grudge against us,
but he's still our Great Leader.

51
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:52,380
I dunno…
that would be a pretty shady move.

52
00:02:52,463 --> 00:02:53,548
On-brand though.

53
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:55,758
Maybe we should dig up
some dirt on the president.

54
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:59,262
Title, "How Many Skeletons
Are In the President's Closet?"

55
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:00,638
'Bout to get yourself in trouble, man.

56
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:01,723
-Come on, guys.
-That's great. Love it.

57
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:03,892
Why mess with a story
that will never see the light of day?

58
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,894
I mean, let's just take him out
and be done with it.

59
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,271
I know you're just joking around,
but that's crossing the line.

60
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:10,565
- Someone could hear you.
- You think I'm joking?

61
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,442
We've been on Trigger for a while.

62
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:14,569
I think I know how to pull off
the perfect crime.

63
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,988
Huh?

64
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:20,283
So where's Ms. Oh? We're supposed
to get our stories straight,

65
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:21,534
but she's still not here.

66
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:24,871
♪ Under his wings ♪

67
00:03:24,954 --> 00:03:26,539
"Memorial Mass for the Victims of
the Painted Flower Kindergarten Accident"

68
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:29,709
♪ I am safely abiding… ♪

69
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:31,252
We dedicate this mass

70
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:34,672
to the angels whose lives
were tragically cut short

71
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,967
in a horrific accident 20 years ago today.

72
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:40,929
In loving memory
of Park Sunjeong Maria,

73
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:42,931
Kim Yeji, Kim Uram,

74
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,769
Chae Yun, Jeon Harin, Shin Yeonu.

75
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:53,191
Let's take this time to say a prayer
for these children's lost souls.

76
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:59,614
♪ Under his wings ♪

77
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:03,785
♪ Under his wings ♪

78
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:05,870
♪ Who from his love can sever? ♪

79
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,914
As always,
we'll be filming this.

80
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:13,836
Something important must've come up.
Hence the camera, right?

81
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,921
"Please Help Find Cha Seongwook"

82
00:04:15,004 --> 00:04:16,881
We've gotten to know
each other pretty well, huh?

83
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,383
So, what do you know?

84
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:20,551
We've found her, sir.

85
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,221
Found her? Found who?

86
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:27,725
Mr. Cha Seongwook's…
his ex-girlfriend.

87
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:35,775
Did you…

88
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,987
Did you really find her?

89
00:04:40,071 --> 00:04:42,198
We did, sir.

90
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,867
There were rumors
that she'd returned to Korea,

91
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,202
that she was living abroad,

92
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:50,373
and as it turns out,
she's been in the States for 20 years.

93
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,250
She even changed her name.

94
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,127
Oh…

95
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:56,838
And did you get in touch with her?

96
00:04:56,921 --> 00:04:57,922
Yes.

97
00:04:58,423 --> 00:04:59,590
Well, indirectly, but still.

98
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,761
I'm going to meet with her.

99
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:05,638
You know, tracking down that woman

100
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,348
might be the breakthrough we need…

101
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,727
if we are ever gonna solve
your son's disappearance.

102
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:16,691
My precious son…

103
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:18,860
Seongwook…

104
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:23,865
Please ask her where he is

105
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,491
and how he's doing.

106
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:30,371
Please ask her for me when you find her.

107
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:31,748
I beg you, please.

108
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,541
Please.

109
00:05:33,624 --> 00:05:34,834
I promise I will.

110
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,295
I'll do just that.

111
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:42,925
Why'd she bring flowers?
This place barely gets any light.

112
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:44,927
What's the matter?
They're the ray of hope we need

113
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,637
in this depressing hole of an office.

114
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:49,307
You would say that.
You'll eat up anything Soryong gives you.

115
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:57,732
- Oh, man.
- Is that nail polish?

116
00:05:58,274 --> 00:06:01,110
Whoa, chief, come on,
why're you giving him such a hard time?

117
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,362
What's wrong?

118
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:06,240
Well, us Gen Z-ers… uh… uh…

119
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,576
I mean, Millennials too…
I guess you wouldn't get it.

120
00:06:08,659 --> 00:06:10,745
It's called
having a sense of style, right?

121
00:06:10,828 --> 00:06:13,539
Hey, man, I wasn't judging,
I was just asking a question.

122
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:15,416
What, I'm not allowed
to ask Millenials questions now?

123
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,126
You could've easily said,

124
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,045
"Well, that's unique"
and just played it cool.

125
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,880
My, you've grown.

126
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,548
Anyway. Here, this is for you.

127
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:23,716
"Trigger: Firing the Bullet of Truth"

128
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,426
They say if you survive
three months on Trigger,

129
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,969
you've basically reached
the Promised Land,

130
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:29,806
but I've been here for three years
and I'm still assistant producer.

131
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:31,265
I have a killer story right here.

132
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,809
So why isn't anyone interested, huh?

133
00:06:32,892 --> 00:06:34,852
Giho, assistant producer's
the best job here.

134
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:35,937
You don't have a clue.

135
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:37,146
"Wife: I sent you the divorce papers."

136
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,773
And neither do I.

137
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:42,735
So, there's this crazy dude who takes
these stray cats and then he's…

138
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,321
You're not gonna open that?

139
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:46,447
Exciting stuff in there.

140
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,866
It's your new ID badge.
Here, check it out.

141
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,701
Oh. Wait, you make this yourself?

142
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:52,036
"Lunatic Han
Soap Opera Department"

143
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:53,871
No, right?

144
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:56,040
What kind of maniac would do that?

145
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:57,208
You're in my personal space.

146
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:02,046
Oh, right… I totally am.

147
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,048
My bad. Sorry, man. Sorry about that…

148
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:06,467
Ah, you're here!

149
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:08,344
Head up to
the President's office right away.

150
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,138
"Lunatic Han
Soap Opera Department"

151
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:11,889
Yes.

152
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,349
Oh. Hello, President Koo.

153
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,475
Yes, I understand.

154
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,279
Did you watch the inauguration?

155
00:07:26,362 --> 00:07:27,738
Oh, yes, of course we did.

156
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:30,324
Wow, you were so charismatic,
you were just…

157
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,453
We haven't met since the move.

158
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:36,122
Didn't want to come empty-handed.

159
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,124
Oh, uh, a sun… a sunflower, huh?

160
00:07:38,207 --> 00:07:40,668
Wow, it's… it's… it's beautiful, huh?

161
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,841
Oh…

162
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:49,343
Ms. Soryong,
instead of thinking up gifts,

163
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:51,345
why don't you try some self-reflection?

164
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:53,222
Parachuting into a cult's headquarters

165
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,975
and you dragged along a rookie
on his first assignment.

166
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:57,768
If this is about me
and my methods, then I--

167
00:07:57,852 --> 00:07:59,020
It might've been the right move.

168
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,355
That story wouldn't have gone anywhere
if you hadn't done it.

169
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,274
That being said, what were you thinking,

170
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,735
letting a porno leak
right before the inauguration?

171
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:07,737
It wasn't a porno,
it was illegal material.

172
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,405
And I should note,
it might've been a deepfake.

173
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:11,866
President Koo,
while we're on the subject,

174
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:14,744
people from all across the country
are flooding our homepage now,

175
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:16,704
so if you could send
some additional resources to--

176
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:18,206
You still don't get it, do you?

177
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,833
-Your show's at risk of cancellation.
-Canc…

178
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:24,128
Uh, President Koo, I mean…
I just think that canceling our show

179
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:26,255
over one incident might be a bit…

180
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,757
-a bit too--
-A bit too harsh?

181
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:31,552
That travel show we canceled had
double the ratings of your pitiful show.

182
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,221
And you scumbags refuse to take ads.

183
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:36,641
The industry's under strain,
but what would you know about that?

184
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:38,392
I don't care how iconic your show is,

185
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:41,437
if you tank our reputation
and don't bring in money, you're done.

186
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:43,898
You think the president
can't do that much?

187
00:08:44,815 --> 00:08:48,319
So you want to cancel our show
over unverified fake news,

188
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:50,947
because we don't bring enough revenue,
and the public's upset?

189
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:52,740
I got that right?

190
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,619
Uh… Let me explain, sir.

191
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:59,413
Ms. Oh isn't quite seeing
the big picture just yet.

192
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:03,834
Soryong, you think you're hot shit
because you run a highly acclaimed show?

193
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:05,628
We've all been there, okay?

194
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:07,880
Trigger's accomplishments
are not your doing.

195
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,758
You're just riding on the coattails
of your seniors' success.

196
00:09:11,425 --> 00:09:13,553
During harder times,
we managed to run a tight ship

197
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:14,887
and avoid these controversies.

198
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:17,306
I'd say we're doing just as well
as our seniors did.

199
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:19,850
Huh.

200
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:23,938
Then how would you like to duke it out
with one of the big dogs?

201
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:27,275
-What?
-You and I will go head-to-head

202
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,943
and we'll see who comes out on top.

203
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:30,903
If I can catch Dr. Trigger first,

204
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,446
then that's a wrap on your show.

205
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:36,075
And in the unlikely event that it's you,
cancellation plans will be paused.

206
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:37,827
You'll get a grace period.
What do you say?

207
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,912
Please, President Koo,
the guys in our department

208
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:43,124
are sleep-deprived enough as it is,
if they have to do this now too--

209
00:09:43,207 --> 00:09:44,625
Getting cold feet?

210
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,502
Why should we keep you around

211
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,963
if you can't even find
a petty criminal like this?

212
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:52,008
Challenge accepted.

213
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:58,556
There'll be no exchange of information
between us.

214
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:00,683
So fair play.

215
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:05,396
What on earth were you thinking,
taking him up on that?

216
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:07,189
I'm gonna investigate
the Cha Seongwook case

217
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,816
while he's busy with Dr. Trigger.

218
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:10,651
Cha…

219
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:12,320
Are you out of your damn mind?

220
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:13,696
I told you a million times to stop!

221
00:10:14,238 --> 00:10:16,115
Look.

222
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:18,326
If he manages to get to our guy first,
then we're totally screwed!

223
00:10:18,409 --> 00:10:20,953
Hey, we're going get him first.

224
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,872
You just said you'd work on Cha Seongwook.

225
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,540
So then who… who… who is "we"?

226
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,417
Me?

227
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,668
For Christ's sakes, I'm the chief.

228
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:30,838
What, you think I'm just farting around
with nothing better to do? Huh?

229
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:33,132
No one ever said you'd do it alone.

230
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:34,216
Think about it.

231
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,969
The Cha Seongwook case is
one of the top unsolved cases in Korea.

232
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:40,181
Not a single show's
dared to touch it for two decades.

233
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:41,807
Who stands to gain the most

234
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:43,601
if we manage to hit a home run?

235
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,729
Cancellation?
They'll beg us for an interview.

236
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,315
I'll ride down with you.

237
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,233
Oh, of course, sir.

238
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,401
Oh, right.

239
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:56,072
Who took over for the producer
who quit over PTSD?

240
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,156
Oh, uh…

241
00:10:57,698 --> 00:11:00,743
Uh, we were actually
just talking about that.

242
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:03,037
How about we let that rookie of yours
try his hand?

243
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:06,123
Sheesh. Isn't this a new building?

244
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:09,502
Uh, is the rookie you're referring to…
Mr. Han?

245
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:12,213
I've talked to him, he's one smart fellow.
Great credentials.

246
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:15,633
Yeah, but still…
I'm not sure somebody so new should be--

247
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:18,719
Your show's about to get canceled,
so why not take a few risks?

