00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:17,456
Whoa, what the…

499
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:18,790
Hey, cut it out. Come on.

500
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:20,459
The cat is mine.

501
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,004
Hey! Let go! Jesus.

502
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:26,298
What the hell? Come on, it's cold out.

503
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:29,050
Just hurry up
and get on home, okay? It's freezing.

504
00:24:37,350 --> 00:24:39,603
-Will you be checking any bags?
-No, no bags.

505
00:24:43,398 --> 00:24:44,816
SEOCHO POLICE STATION
ANNAM POLICE PRECINCT

506
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,819
Oh.

507
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:49,321
Oh…

508
00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:53,450
Hey, aren't you
the host from Trigger?

509
00:24:53,533 --> 00:24:55,285
- That's me.
- Holy crap, no fricking way!

510
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:57,162
I'm a huge fan of your work!
Like, your biggest fan!

511
00:24:57,245 --> 00:24:59,456
I've watched every episode
that's ever aired! This is incredible!

512
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:00,540
I appreciate that.

513
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:03,168
-Wow.
-Uh, thanks for your hard work, officers.

514
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:08,131
Okay, um…
yeah, so this prick…

515
00:25:08,215 --> 00:25:09,925
I mean, this, uh, TV producer…

516
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:16,306
You feel wronged?

517
00:25:17,057 --> 00:25:18,642
To be fair, judging by the footage,

518
00:25:18,725 --> 00:25:20,685
they had every reason to suspect you.

519
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:22,938
If you're gonna feed
stray cats, do it out in the open.

520
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:24,022
Be proud of it.

521
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,274
You don't seem to care
what people think anyway.

522
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:27,859
I just wanna live
a long, quiet life, okay?

523
00:25:27,943 --> 00:25:29,528
I'm not trying to do good deeds.

524
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,696
But anyway, thank you.

525
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:33,365
I'll pay you back somehow.

526
00:25:33,448 --> 00:25:34,991
No need for that.

527
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:37,786
I'll be there
whether it's the 10th or 100th time.

528
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:41,081
That is in the job description, after all.

529
00:25:45,752 --> 00:25:47,546
I'm starting to like you, Mr. Han.

530
00:25:55,971 --> 00:25:58,932
Think of sunflowers. Pretty, right?

531
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:16,032
Exquisite flowers bloom from their center,
but still they pretend to have thorns.

532
00:26:17,033 --> 00:26:19,369
You're a little like that,
so prickly with everyone.

533
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:20,996
It's almost like you wanna get hurt.

534
00:26:21,788 --> 00:26:24,124
The point is, I don't care
if you pee-bombed someone.

535
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:25,667
Or were a nepo hire.

536
00:26:26,376 --> 00:26:27,544
Let's be a team.

537
00:26:31,172 --> 00:26:32,382
I'm not pretending.

538
00:26:33,049 --> 00:26:36,219
I've been screwed over so many times
that I have trouble trusting people.

539
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:38,555
I flat-out don't trust people, actually.

540
00:26:41,558 --> 00:26:44,102
So do me a favor and warn me
before you get all soft like that.

541
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:45,520
'Cause if you keep that up…

542
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,273
I might start trusting again.

543
00:27:02,912 --> 00:27:05,373
This building belongs to
a delinquent landlord!

544
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:07,000
I can't give you back the deposit.
Keep the place.

545
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:10,337
Rental Scam Property

546
00:27:11,921 --> 00:27:14,299
Jang Hakui

547
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:15,425
I can't give you back the deposit…

548
00:27:36,321 --> 00:27:37,322
That's cute.

549
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:38,531
"Thirst, Mother, The Unjust"

550
00:27:55,548 --> 00:27:57,050
There he is again.

551
00:27:58,593 --> 00:28:00,011
-No, Dad, don't! Stop it!
-Stay still! I said, stay still!

552
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:02,597
How dare you steal?
Did you forget your dad's a cop?

553
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:04,974
I told you to stay still!
Why won't you listen to me?

554
00:28:05,058 --> 00:28:06,935
-Hyung said I had to!
-Why, you little shit!

555
00:28:07,018 --> 00:28:08,228
I promise, he made me!

556
00:28:08,311 --> 00:28:10,355
- Just say you're sorry!
- Stay still.

557
00:28:10,438 --> 00:28:13,608
-Just tell your father you're sorry!
-Hyung, why aren't you saying anything?

558
00:28:13,692 --> 00:28:15,276
I told you to stay still.

559
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,945
- Damn it, I said stay still!
- Hyung!

560
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:18,321
Hyung!

561
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:19,781
Hyung!

562
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,912
Hakuna matata.

563
00:28:29,791 --> 00:28:31,793
Hakuna matata.

564
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:36,548
Oh, my gosh, what is this?

565
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:40,343
Again? My God,
what kind of sick maniac would do this?

566
00:28:40,427 --> 00:28:43,388
Oh, my God,
this time it was a mother and kitten!

567
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:45,348
And they sewed their eyes shut.

568
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:46,766
What is happening in this country?

569
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:48,727
Why won't they do something
about the mentally ill?

570
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:50,812
Those poor things.

571
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:53,064
Don't you think we should call the cops?

572
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:54,983
What kind of monster
could do such a thing?

573
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:57,026
Hey, hey. Do you really
have to take a photo of that?

574
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,903
You have no idea
how many views this'll get.

575
00:29:00,905 --> 00:29:03,366
That's just disgusting.
Keep walking, kids.

576
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:04,909
Nothing to see here. Go on.

577
00:29:16,463 --> 00:29:18,047
Hey! I could charge you!

578
00:29:18,131 --> 00:29:20,300
Officer! Anyone call in
a cat-related incident?

579
00:29:20,383 --> 00:29:22,469
Are you just barging in here
and asking questions?

580
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:23,803
That cat yesterday.

581
00:29:24,637 --> 00:29:27,182
It's been murdered.
They found its body next to its mother.

582
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:28,391
We've gotten reports,

583
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:31,102
chopped-up cats have been turning up
around the neighborhood.

584
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:33,146
Whoa, whoa, hold on, hold on.

585
00:29:33,229 --> 00:29:34,773
I hear you,
a cat's been killed.

586
00:29:34,856 --> 00:29:36,441
Understood. What do you want us to do?

587
00:29:36,524 --> 00:29:37,609
What do you mean?

588
00:29:37,692 --> 00:29:40,320
People can't just do that to an animal!

589
00:29:40,403 --> 00:29:43,072
All right, do you see
what we're dealing with over here?

590
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:44,908
I understand that you're an animal lover,

591
00:29:44,991 --> 00:29:47,994
but unless it's a mass-killing situation,
a few animal deaths don't matter.

592
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:49,996
I mean, it's not
as though you saw the perpetrator.

593
00:29:50,079 --> 00:29:51,956
You think this psycho
who killed these animals

594
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:53,875
doesn't have it in him
to kill a human, huh?

595
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:56,252
Lady, come on!

596
00:29:56,336 --> 00:29:57,545
You can't do that here!

597
00:29:57,629 --> 00:30:00,465
Ugh, come on, let's get you
to the… the bathroom. Hurry up!

598
00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:22,403
Oh, Jesus, how long was I out?

599
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,489
-You're back from the States?
-Wake up, get it together.

600
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:27,534
I didn't go to the States,
it's only been a day.

601
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:28,618
Whoa, really?

602
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:30,703
Oh, man, you threw me off.

603
00:30:34,582 --> 00:30:37,293
Oh, so, um, yesterday,
while I was researching,

604
00:30:37,377 --> 00:30:38,711
I logged onto the dark web.

605
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:40,839
Man, it's scary out there.

606
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:42,674
Like, animal abuse forums?

607
00:30:42,757 --> 00:30:44,592
One look
and you'll lose faith in humanity.

608
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:46,761
People can be straight-up evil.

609
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:48,346
-This is it here?
-Yeah, that one.

610
00:30:48,429 --> 00:30:49,597
That's not it.

611
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:54,769
Serial Cat Killer of Seocho-gu

612
00:30:54,853 --> 00:30:57,397
Is this your way
of getting back at them for yesterday?

613
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,315
Or are you collaborating with Giho?

614
00:31:00,066 --> 00:31:01,985
I didn't ask you
to write a pitch for this story.

615
00:31:02,068 --> 00:31:04,153
What do you mean? Collaborating?

616
00:31:04,237 --> 00:31:05,530
The cat from yesterday

617
00:31:05,613 --> 00:31:07,490
and its mother was killed.

618
00:31:07,574 --> 00:31:10,159
They were both viciously slaughtered
and left out on the street.

619
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:12,829
Whoever did this, they're not even human.

620
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:13,913
Hey, what are you even…

621
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:15,957
Are you talking about
that cat story from the internet?

622
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:18,084
The police don't care
because they're just cats.

623
00:31:18,668 --> 00:31:20,295
This psycho needs to be exposed,

624
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:22,714
and it's our responsibility
to do it on the show.

625
00:31:23,506 --> 00:31:24,799
Hey, wait…

626
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,926
Did you… read my pitch?

627
00:31:28,303 --> 00:31:29,304
Did I what?

628
00:31:29,387 --> 00:31:31,180
Look, it's almost identical to mine.

629
00:31:31,764 --> 00:31:32,807
I'm not a mind reader.

630
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:34,851
How would I possibly know
what's in your pitch?

631
00:31:34,934 --> 00:31:37,020
Whatever, man, just come out
and admit it if you copied it!

632
00:31:37,103 --> 00:31:38,855
- But I didn't copy you!
- Well, you must have!

633
00:31:38,938 --> 00:31:40,648
What's wrong with you?
You still half-asleep?

634
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:42,525
What are you talking about?
Your proposal is exactly the same as mine!

635
00:31:42,609 --> 00:31:44,527
And why do you keep
putting your feet up on my chair?

636
00:31:44,611 --> 00:31:45,778
-What the hell are you talking--
-You're completely insane!

637
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:46,946
Come on, come on.

638
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:48,323
Calm it down, okay?

639
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:51,659
What a lively crew we've got.
And it's still only morning.

640
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:54,329
Conference room, now.

641
00:31:57,916 --> 00:32:00,752
All right, so, about Mr. Han's story…

642
00:32:03,838 --> 00:32:06,341
These cats are getting killed
left and right,

643
00:32:06,424 --> 00:32:09,260
but the perpetrator's hard to catch,
and it's unclear how he'd be charged,

644
00:32:09,344 --> 00:32:11,179
so the cops aren't doing anything.

645
00:32:11,262 --> 00:32:13,973
If we could unmask the killer live,
it'd get tons of attention,

646
00:32:14,849 --> 00:32:17,393
and I'm guessing they'd stop
for fear of getting doxxed.

647
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:21,940
Mr. Han may seem agitated,

648
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:23,816
he was framed
as the cat killer last night.

649
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,443
I'm not agitated, I'm outraged!

650
00:32:25,526 --> 00:32:27,487
And not because
I got framed as the killer.

651
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:30,740
This is my brain's natural response
after seeing the sick and terrible things

652
00:32:30,823 --> 00:32:31,824
done to those poor cats.

653
00:32:31,908 --> 00:32:33,368
Putting all of that aside,

654
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:35,578
this talk of unmasking the killer,

655
00:32:35,662 --> 00:32:37,497
that's absolutely not what we do here.

656
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:38,748
I like it.

657
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:41,000
I gotta say, it's more topical

658
00:32:41,084 --> 00:32:43,252
than a 20-year-old missing person's case.

659
00:32:44,003 --> 00:32:45,755
- Give it a go.
- Come on now, sir!

660
00:32:45,838 --> 00:32:47,048
Lower your voice.

661
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,008
I'm not one of your underlings.

662
00:32:54,722 --> 00:32:57,976
Trigger's internal policy
is that we put aside hierarchy

663
00:32:58,059 --> 00:32:59,519
when it comes to debating what we cover.

664
00:33:00,311 --> 00:33:03,773
Not once have we ever chosen a story
just because a higher-up told us to.

665
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:06,442
I don't know how it was
in the newsroom though.

666
00:33:06,526 --> 00:33:07,652
Excuse me, sir.

667
00:33:09,737 --> 00:33:11,322
This is a proposal I wrote.
Please have a look.

668
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:13,783
- Kang Giho.
- Oh, Mr. Kang?

669
00:33:13,866 --> 00:33:15,243
Why are you handing me this?

670
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:16,411
Uh, so the…

671
00:33:18,287 --> 00:33:23,167
Um… the, uh… the cat incident,
I was actually on that story first.

672
00:33:23,251 --> 00:33:24,252
If you look at my proposal--

673
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:25,420
So work together.

674
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:28,589
Use your AP chops
to help Mr. Han with his segment.

675
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:29,966
Sir?

676
00:33:30,049 --> 00:33:32,051
You're an associate producer, no?

677
00:33:32,135 --> 00:33:34,095
Bold move listing these credentials.

678
00:33:35,221 --> 00:33:37,807
We don't exactly require
a degree from the top schools,

679
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:40,184
but we do have some standards.

680
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:42,895
And here you are,
listing a college I've never heard of.

681
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:52,655
Sir, I assumed you of all people
would give respect to my staff.

682
00:33:52,739 --> 00:33:54,532
But apparently I was wrong.

683
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:56,701
I won't stand for this.

684
00:33:58,745 --> 00:34:01,789
I've taped our conversation
from yesterday, so if you keep this up,

685
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:03,875
I'll go public about the cancellation,

686
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:06,210
about everything we discussed,

687
00:34:07,128 --> 00:34:08,838
and let the police handle Dr. Trigger.

688
00:34:08,921 --> 00:34:10,757
That seems like a much simpler solution.

689
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:25,229
Cancellation? Did I hear that?

690
00:34:26,856 --> 00:34:28,900
Uh, what just… Oh.

691
00:34:33,613 --> 00:34:34,614
Oh. Hi, sir.

692
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:37,909
-How are we doing?
-I suggest you keep your staff in line.

693
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,543
I truly had no idea.

694
00:34:47,627 --> 00:34:50,129
I don't even really care about this stuff.

695
00:34:50,213 --> 00:34:51,923
I just wanted to catch the killer that--

696
00:34:52,006 --> 00:34:53,466
But that's even worse.

697
00:34:53,549 --> 00:34:55,927
My dream is to produce my own stories.

698
00:34:57,095 --> 00:35:01,224
What you just said makes it
even more humiliating and hurtful.

699
00:35:02,141 --> 00:35:04,143
At least pretend you want this job.

700
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:15,571
Why the roof?

701
00:35:20,701 --> 00:35:22,120
Ms. Oh…

702
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:24,914
Do you think I'm stupid too?

703
00:35:24,997 --> 00:35:27,083
You never ever
take my calls, do you?

704
00:35:27,875 --> 00:35:30,128
I just climbed nine flights of stairs.

705
00:35:30,211 --> 00:35:31,587
I couldn't talk on the phone.

706
00:35:31,671 --> 00:35:33,506
Why didn't you just take the elevator?

707
00:35:35,675 --> 00:35:37,218
You could've just taken the elevator,

708
00:35:37,301 --> 00:35:39,178
you didn't have to walk up
all those stairs.

709
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,608
Are you done crying?

710
00:35:52,692 --> 00:35:54,360
I'm not even halfway done.

711
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:56,696
Have you considered grad school?

712
00:35:58,573 --> 00:36:00,825
I could probably help you
with some of the tuition.

713
00:36:04,078 --> 00:36:06,914
We're supposed to be
in the AI brave new world by now.

714
00:36:07,790 --> 00:36:09,750
And this place is stuck in the past.

715
00:36:11,127 --> 00:36:12,461
All style and no substance.

716
00:36:12,545 --> 00:36:15,006
It's no wonder everybody's
always trash-talking the media.

717
00:36:17,091 --> 00:36:20,219
So are we… gonna get canceled?

718
00:36:26,142 --> 00:36:28,644
That guy Han, first he reminded me
of a cat, you know what I mean?

719
00:36:28,728 --> 00:36:30,229
'Cause he's petty and feline,

720
00:36:30,813 --> 00:36:32,857
but turns out he's a cold-hearted snake.

721
00:36:32,940 --> 00:36:35,610
And you seriously gave up
your big America trip for that?

722
00:36:36,152 --> 00:36:37,653
Are you crazy?

723
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:39,572
Why would I give up on
Cha Seongwook because of Han?

724
00:36:39,655 --> 00:36:40,698
Then why stay?

725
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:45,912
My Cha Seongwook contact got in touch.

726
00:36:49,582 --> 00:36:52,627
BlueBeard: Give me a few days
to bring Cho Haewon to Korea.

727
00:36:52,710 --> 00:36:54,587
I got Han's call soon after that.

728
00:36:55,254 --> 00:36:56,380
Hey, Mr. Han.

729
00:36:57,965 --> 00:36:59,091
Wha… Whoa, you mean…

730
00:36:59,175 --> 00:37:02,595
Cho… Cho Haewon, the… the woman
who used to go out with Cha Seongwook?

731
00:37:03,804 --> 00:37:05,056
That's crazy.

732
00:37:06,807 --> 00:37:08,643
I'm gonna hit this out of the park.

733
00:37:10,144 --> 00:37:11,395
No one's canceling Trigger.

734
00:37:14,106 --> 00:37:15,233
Don't sweat it, okay?

735
00:37:15,316 --> 00:37:18,236
You're a sparkling, pretty little thing.
Don't let the school stuff get you down.

736
00:37:19,195 --> 00:37:20,613
Believe me, I don't want it to.

737
00:37:22,865 --> 00:37:25,618
And it's a misunderstanding,
the Han Do thing.

738
00:37:26,118 --> 00:37:28,496
He's not the kind of guy
who would steal someone's work.

739
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:29,747
Whoa, hold on a minute.

740
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:31,415
How are you…

741
00:37:32,041 --> 00:37:33,417
Are you seriously siding with him now?

742
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:36,337
Man, I feel like
I'm totally alone in this!

743
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:37,630
I mean, how?

744
00:37:37,713 --> 00:37:39,340
You've only known the guy for a few days.

745
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:40,424
